commitResults.messageBody: Note: find command has no prefix!

commitResults.messageTitle: Create ExportComand and ExportGenerator classes. ExportCommand executes to initate the export process to write FoodRecord to a file, ExportGenerator peforms String formatting and file writing itself. Improved FoodRecord toString method to give line-by-line Food entries Auto-sorting now done after every update of Food.

Implemented 2nd find command extension: Categorical Find. Users can now find using a SINGLE specified field, choosing only one parameter. This parameter can be ANY one of the following in the FORMAT below. Format: find [n/NAME] [cal/CALORIES] [p/PROTEIN] [c/CARBOHYDRATE] [f/FAT] [t/TAG] For NAME and TAG, substring search is implemented, and exact search is implemented for CALORIES, PROTEIN, CARBOHYDRATE, and FAT.

Update UG for find, list, export commands. - Now left with GUI screenshots to demonstrate examples. Update UG Introduction to be a user-centric mini marketing stint. Update UG FAQ for transferring Calgo data and export & report file locations.

Fix critical bugs: #1 leading zeros & #2 nutritional values beyond integer maximum. Calorie, Protein, Carbohydrate, Fat are now all non-negative Integers within 5 digits and cannot be blank. Rationale: Human diets are near impossible to exceed 5 digits. Each gram of Protein gives 4 cal, Carbohydrate gives 4 cal, Fat gives 9 cal. These values will always be smaller than total Calories. Edit UG part on find command to include 5 digits restriction.
